728248f-a.title: Queens: Wyckoff Avenue - Decatur Street
728248f-a.text:
Wyckoff Ave., south side, between Decatur Street (left) and Norman Sto, (rimht), showing the different buildings of Frank Albrecht, florist. At the extreme left is the smoke stack of the Malt Distase Company.
This is a set of two views.
April 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

728249f-a.title: Queens: Wyckoff Avenue - Decatur Street
728249f-a.text:
Wyckoff Avenue (right), south side, west of Decatur Street (center of view, showing at the S.W. corner of Decatur Street and Wvcloff Ave. the Diogenes Brewery Building, once a part of the Malt Diastase Company (erected in 1898). On the other side of the street is the Socony Station. The 2-story frame house seen beyond the brewery building is 1052 Wyckoff
Ave.
April 1929.
Eumene L. Armbruster Collection.
